programme.title: The Hobbit: Battle Of The Five Armies
programme.desc: In the exciting final chapter of "The Hobbit" series, Bilbo Baggins and his traveling companions get caught up in a war that threatens to destroy all of Middle Earth

programme.title: Law & Order
programme.desc: Obsession. A radio-show host is killed and suspicion falls on his attractive widow, who's set to inherit $20 million, and two of the woman's lovers

programme.title: Law & Order
programme.desc: Possession. When the lone remaining resident of an upper West Side apartment building is found murdered outside her door, Briscoe and Green attempt to sort through her longstanding battle with the landlord in the hopes of finding a credible suspect

programme.title: Law & Order
programme.desc: Formerly Famous. Gary Busey plays a former singer whose wife is found shot to death blocks from the restaurant where they had just finished dinner. Arthur Cahill: Joe Piscopo. Brad Feldman: Bruce Altman. Peter Vega: David Allen Case. Jason Vega: Nathan J. Wetherington. Briscoe: Jerry Orbach. Green: Jesse L. Martin. McCoy: Sam Waterston

programme.title: Arrow
programme.desc: Beacon of Hope. Brie Larvan breaks out of jail and turns up at Palmer Tech threatening to kill everyone unless she gets the bio-chip that is implanted in Felicity's spine. Meanwhile, Oliver looks to a surprising ally to help rescue Felicity, Thea and Donna who are trapped in Palmer Tech with everyone else

programme.title: Charmed
programme.desc: Ex Libris. College student Phoebe (Alyssa Milano) comes to the aid of the ghost of her fellow student Charlene (Rebecca Cross), who was killed because of her master's thesis, which exposed the demon Libris (Scott Lincoln). Elsewhere, Prue (Shannen Doherty) tries to help a grieving father track down his daughter's murderer. And while endeavoring to book the Goo Goo Dolls for the P3 club, Piper (Holly Marie Combs) is rudely informed by Dan (Greg Vaughan) that Leo (Brian Krause) may already be married

programme.title: Charmed
programme.desc: Astral Monkey. A doctor investigating the sisters' strange talents imbues three monkeys with their abilities, then accidentally receives all their powers at once, which threatens to drive him mad

programme.title: Charmed
programme.desc: Apocalypse, Not. The Charmed Ones find some unlikely allies when Prue gets stuck in a vortex with one of the Horsemen of the Apocalypse, causing the two groups to unite

programme.title: Supernatural
programme.desc: Thin Lizzie. Sam and Dean investigate a series of murders at a local B&B that also happens to be Lizzie Borden's old home

programme.title: Supernatural
programme.desc: Our Little World. Castiel seeks Metatron's help to stop the Darkness. However, Metatron is pretty happy with his new life as a freelance videographer for the local news and isn't inclined to help the Winchesters or Castiel. Meanwhile, Crowley loses his hold on Amara

programme.title: Supernatural
programme.desc: Plush. Sheriff Donna calls Sam and Dean for help after a horrific murder with supernatural elements occurs in her town. Meanwhile, Sam continues to have visions and asks God for help, which frustrates Dean

programme.title: Jack the Giant Slayer
programme.desc: A young farmhand comes into possession of some magic beans but, when planted, they open up a gateway to a land inhabited by angry giants

programme.title: Star Wars Episode V: The Empire Strikes Back
programme.desc: Luke Skywalker takes further Jedi lessons from the venerable Yoda, while Darth Vader continues to pursue his nemesis, in the ice world of Hoth and beyond. Terrific action sequences at the start and imaginative Oedipal encounters at the close make this movie perhaps the best of the Star Wars bunch, or so the real diehards will tell you. Luke comes of age but Han Solo and Princess Leia have their work cut out after Vader's forces, led by the sinister Boba Fett, pursue the Millennium Falcon

programme.title: Star Wars : Return of the Jedi
programme.desc: The rebels attempt to destroy the second powerful Death Star and Luke Skywalker confronts his father, Darth Vader who demands that he joins the dark side, under orders of the Emperor

programme.title: Animal Kingdom
programme.desc: Eat What You Kill. A risky heist misfires and the boys blame Smurf, sending shock waves through the family, in the Season 2 premiere. Also: Baz deals with being a single parent; and Deran plans for the future

programme.title: Animal Kingdom
programme.desc: Eat What You Kill. A risky heist misfires and the boys blame Smurf, sending shock waves through the family, in the Season 2 premiere. Also: Baz deals with being a single parent; and Deran plans for the future

programme.title: Law & Order
programme.desc: The Sixth Man. McCoy and Borgia prosecute a famous basketball player accused of murdering a fan who had been harassing him for some time. They find the star's fingerprints in the victim's apartment, but the evidence linking him to the crime scene is dismissed as inadmissible because the detectives cut corners to find a match on the police database

programme.title: Law & Order
programme.desc: License to Kill. A car chase through Manhattan leaves one man dead and a teenager injured; leading Fontana and Green to discover the victim was being followed after massacring a hunting party. As the man who led the chase is publicly lauded for his brave efforts, McCoy and Borgia make their case that his poor decisions only endangered other lives

programme.title: The Last Ship
programme.desc: Pilot - Phase Six. The fate of mankind rests on the crew of a lone naval ship when the world is gripped by a deadly virus

programme.title: The Last Ship
programme.desc: Welcome to Gitmo. The crew members arrive at the Guantanamo Bay military base to collect food, fuel and medical supplies. When they come under attack by escaped Gitmo prisoners, they team up with a gruff private contractor to push back against the offensive

programme.title: The Last Ship
programme.desc: Dead Reckoning. The crew faces a new foe targeting Rachel and her research, leading Chandler to engage in a series of dangerous strategic manoeuvres

programme.title: The Last Ship
programme.desc: We'll Get There. Chandler's leadership is put to the test when the ship's propulsion system is in danger of breaking down, the crew becomes overworked and exhausted, and Dr. Scott could potentially lose all of her research on the virus

programme.title: Law & Order
programme.desc: Myth of Fingerprints. A murder investigation uncovers deliberately faulty forensics in the wrongful conviction of two men 12 years earlier in the case that paved the way for Van Buren's promotion

programme.title: Arrow
programme.desc: Eleven-Fifty-Nine. Oliver and Diggle learn that Merlyn plans to break Darhk out of prison. Meanwhile, Laurel gets a surprising offer and Felicity has a heart to heart talk with Curtis

programme.title: Charmed
programme.sub-title: Be Careful What You Witch For
programme.desc: Be Careful What You Witch For. In Charmed's second-season finale, French Stewart guest stars as a glib genie who offers to grant the most fondly held wishes of the three Halliwell girls. Alas, in each case there is a "catch." Wishing to relive her first love, Prue (Shannen Doherty) regresses into an obnoxious teenager (a sly comment on actress Doherty's prickly reputation on the set of Beverly Hills 90210). Phoebe (Alyssa Milano) wants to have the power of flight, but then can't deal with the consequences. And Piper (Holly Marie Combs) desires nothing more than for Dan (Greg Vaughan) to forget about her and move on with his life -- but in the process of "moving on," Dan rapidly grows older and older before her eyes. Worst of all, Prue is attacked by the Dragon Warlock (Marcus Graham), who is in cahoots with the duplicitous genie-- and the other Halliwell girls are powerless to save their sister from certain death!

programme.title: Charmed
programme.desc: Honeymoon's Over. Barenaked Ladies perform at the sisters' club; Prue and Phoebe capture a demonically possessed killer, only to watch him beat the murder charge in court, due in part to their inability to explain what happened to the murder weapon. Prue: Shannon Doherty. Phoebe: Alyssa Milano. Piper: Holly Marie Combs

programme.title: Charmed
programme.desc: Magic Hour. The Charmed Ones search for a way to let Piper and Leo marry without angering the whitelighter's celestial superiors, who have promised "unspeakable wrath" if the two wed. Meanwhile, the sisters try to aid a man who is cursed to be an owl for 12 hours a day

programme.title: Supernatural
programme.desc: Just My Imagination. Sam is shocked when his imaginary childhood friend, Sully, makes an unexpected appearance. Sam tries to understand why he is seeing Sully now. Even more surprising, Dean can see him too

programme.title: Supernatural
programme.desc: O Brother Where Art Thou?. Amara unleashes her power on local townspeople and issues a shocking challenge. Dean tries to better understand the hold Amara has on him, while Sam and Crowley come up with a plan that could have disastrous consequences

programme.title: Supernatural
programme.desc: The Devil in the Details. Lucifer offers Sam a way out of the cage, but it comes with a steep price. Meanwhile, Dean and Castiel look into the angel smiting that could have killed Amara

programme.title: Supernatural
programme.desc: Into the Mystic. Sam and Dean investigate a case in which people suffer violent deaths after hearing a mysterious song

programme.title: Bones
programme.desc: The Princess and the Pear. Agent Perotta (Marisa Coughlan) pitches in when the Jeffersonian team investigates the death of a female science-fiction fan, which leads to a visit to a convention for aficionados of comic books and video games

programme.title: Die Hard With a Vengeance
programme.desc: Cop John McClane teams with a shop owner to outwit a terrorist who is making him perform a series of dangerous tasks all around Manhattan

programme.title: Eagle Eye
programme.desc: Two strangers become pawns in a diabolical plot and must work together to discover what is really happening while trying to prove that they are not terrorists. Shia LaBeouf ("Disturbia") and Michelle Monaghan star in this taut suspense thriller. Michael Chiklis, Rosario Dawson, Billy Bob Thornton. Directed by D.J. Caruso

programme.title: Rush Hour 2
programme.desc: Director Brett Ratner is reunited with stars Jackie Chan and Chris Tucker in this all-action sequel. This time, they're on Chan's turf, in China, for a well-earned rest but the murder of US Customs men by one of the most powerful Triad gangsters in Asia sees them back in the thick of things, in the company of femme fatale Zhang Ziyi and secret-service agent Roselyn Sanchez. Some Mandarin/Cantonese with English subtitles

programme.title: Rush Hour
programme.desc: The fastest hands in the East meet the biggest mouth in the West when legendary martial arts daredevil Jackie Chan teams with comedic powerhouse Chris Tucker in Rush Hour. When Hong Kong police detective inspector Lee's favourite pupil is kidnapped in America, the dedicated cop and martial arts genius travels to the United States to find her. Unhappy to have a meddling outsider, the FBI assigns reckless, arrogant and infuriating LAPD detective James Carter to baby-sit Lee--and keep him away from the investigation. But these two very different cops will stop at nothing to find the missing girl
